profile_positions.description:
•	Leading in the technical and strategic management of projects, including design, initiation, planning, budgeting, execution, monitoring and closing;
•	Overseeing effective and efficient project execution to ensure all activities occur according to the planned timeline and on budget;
•	Having overall stewardship of quality management, ensuring that all deliverables are of sufficient standard and align with the strategic objectives of HiiL;
•	Having overall stewardship of risk management; identifying, analyzing and planning for project related risks;
•	Coordinating with the Monitoring, Evaluation & Learning Department to contribute to results-based monitoring, evaluations, outcome-based reporting and the active integration of lessons learned into future programming;
•	Contributing to an enabling environment for on the job capacity development for project staff;
•	Undertaking in-country missions to field sites where required, to monitor project implementation, bolster quality assurance and strengthen relations with local implementing partners; 
•	Ensuring proper documentation throughout all phases of the project cycle; as required by donors, beneficiaries, HiiL and other project stakeholders;
•	Contributing to identifying and securing technical expertise as and when required throughout project duration

1) Strategic program management of the LIVE-UP program
• Lead in the technical and strategic management of project design, work planning, budgeting,
procurement, and impact monitoring of project activities in the field;
• Oversee effective and efficient execution of project activities by working in close collaboration
with the relevant institutions and project teams, at the national and local levels;
• Coordinate results-based monitoring, evaluations and outcome-based reporting, including
ensuring proper baselines, mid-term monitoring, and final evaluations;
• Provide advisory services to national and local institutions, including support to policy processes,
technical advice and support to seminars, trainings and on-the-job capacity development in urban
land, planning, housing and basic services.

2) Ensure coordination and cooperation between program activities/outputs/outcomes and
related local, regional and international development efforts
• Lead in building and maintaining strong relationships and coordination with partners (UN,
government, I/NGO) at city, national, regional and global levels;
• Support improved coordination of UN activities in Afghanistan, including contributing to the
UNDAF and joint integrated work plans with program-related inputs and monitoring;
• Support the promotion of sustainable urbanization and adequate shelter for all in Afghanistan;

3) Contribute to UN-Habitat's support to the Government of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan
• Support the GoIRA with resource mobilization by identifying new programmatic opportunities,
developing concept notes and project documents, and building partnerships with donors and
partners;
